"title": "5707: male and female",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5707",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God created humanity as male and female. Although gender differences are evident in behaviour and role, Scripture teaches the equality and complementarity of the sexes.</p>\n<h2>The creation of male and female</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:20–2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:2\">GEN 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>The fall disrupted relationships between male and female</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:14-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:14–3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:19\">2SA 13:1–13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:3-Prov5:14\">PRO 5:3–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28\">MAT 5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a></p>\n<h2>The equality of male and female</h2>\n<h3>Equality under many old covenant regulations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:5-Num5:7\">NUM 5:5–5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10-Lev20:12\">LEV 20:10–20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:1-Num5:4\">NUM 5:1–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:15\">DEU 15:12–15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:17-Deut23:18\">DEU 23:17–23:18</a></p>\n<h3>Equality in religious observance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:22\">EXO 35:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:4\">NUM 6:1–6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:12\">DEU 31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:19\">2SA 6:19</a></p>\n<h3>Equality of accountability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:21\">LAM 2:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:27\">LEV 20:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15-2Chr36:17\">2CH 36:15–36:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:11\">ACT 5:1–5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Equality in Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26-Gal3:28\">GAL 3:26–3:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17-Acts2:18\">ACT 2:17–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28-Joel2:29\">JOL 2:28–2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:11-1Cor11:12\">1CO 11:11–11:12</a></p>\n<h2>Variations in the treatment of male and female</h2>\n<h3>In OT patriarchal society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:1-Lev27:7\">LEV 27:1–27:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:9–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:1-Exod13:2\">EXO 13:1–13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:14-Exod13:15\">EXO 13:14–13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:14-Num3:15\">NUM 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:11-Num5:31\">NUM 5:11–5:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:8-Num18:10\">NUM 18:8–18:10</a></p>\n<h3>In legislation protecting women under the old covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:7\">NUM 27:1–27:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:1-Num36:12\">NUM 36:1–36:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:19\">DEU 22:13–22:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:25-Deut22:29\">DEU 22:25–22:29</a></p>\n<h3>In roles within the NT church community</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:33-1Cor14:35\">1CO 14:33–14:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3-1Cor11:10\">1CO 11:3–11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:24\">EPH 5:22–5:24</a> <em>The idea of “headship” is complex, but is generally regarded as including the ideas of responsibility and authority within a relationship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:11-1Tim2:15\">1TI 2:11–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:1-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:1–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>In behaviour within the NT church community</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:8-1Tim2:10\">1TI 2:8–2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3-1Cor11:16\">1CO 11:3–11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1-1Tim5:2\">1TI 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Male and female roles within marriage</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:1-1Cor7:7\">1CO 7:1–7:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:31\">PRO 31:10–31:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:22–5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18-Col3:19\">COL 3:18–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:1–3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Male and female imagery used of God</h2>\n<h3>Female imagery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:37\">MAT 23:37</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34\">LUK 13:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:1-Prov8:11\">PRO 8:1–8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:12-Isa66:13\">ISA 66:12–66:13</a></p>\n<h3>Male imagery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:2\">PSA 47:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:3\">EXO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:1\">PSA 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:6\">MAT 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11-Luke11:13\">LUK 11:11–11:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:11\">MAT 7:9–7:11</a></p>",
